    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sancte et individue trinitatis. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/521">Fredericus</persName> secundus divina favente
                        clementia Romanorum <rs key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs> semper augustus et rex
                        Sicilie imperpetuum. Quia ecclesiasticis institutis proficimus, merito
                        ecclesiasticis profectibus insistimus. Cunctis igitur deo nobisque nunc et
                        in posterum militantibus pateat nos pro anime nostre futura recompensatione.
                            <orgName key="#Mother_churches #Bishops" ref="#juridical_persons/404"
                            >Yporiensi ecclesie</orgName> omnem eiusdem <geogName
                            key="#Cities #Comitatus" ref="#estates/258"><placeName
                                key="#Cities #Comitatus #Mother_churches #Bishops" ref="#places/563"
                                >civitatis</placeName></geogName>
                        <rs key="#Districtio">districtum</rs>, <rs key="#Fodrum">fodrum</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Teloneum">theloneum</rs> et omnem publicam functionem atque
                        forinsecus circumcirca per tria miliaria testimonio et auctoritate presentis
                        pagine insignite nostre maiestatid sigillo <rs key="#Imperial/royal_diploma"
                            >concessisse</rs>, donasse, tradidisse, confirmasse et coroborasse atque
                        ad habendum firmiter statuisse cum <rs key="#Curtes">curte</rs> una
                            <geogName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Profits_of_justice #Districtio"
                            ref="#estates/400"><placeName ref="#places/833"
                                key="#Uncertain_tradition #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Profits_of_justice #Districtio"
                                >Romano</placeName></geogName> dicta sub titutlo acquisitionis sibi
                        pertinente et altera <geogName
                            key="#Uncertain_tradition #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Profits_of_justice #Districtio"
                            ref="#estates/401"><placeName ref="#places/834"
                                key="#Uncertain_tradition #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Profits_of_justice #Districtio"
                                >Florano</placeName></geogName> nominata cum omnbus earum
                        pertinentiis, familiis seu capistraticis, successionibus, bannis et ceteris
                        omnibus, que ad <rs key="#Comitatus">comitatum</rs> seu contile pertinent
                        vel pertinere possent, eo videlicet ordine, quatenus <persName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#people/522">Obertus</persName> venerabilis <rs
                            key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs> et presens provisor eiusdem ecclesie et
                        cuncti pro tempore ibidem locandi predictum districtum cum iamdictis
                        curtibus et publicis functionibus, earum pertinentiis et adiacentiis
                        omnibusque aliis supradictis habeant, teneant firmiterque possideant
                        habeantque licentiam legales seu duellares questiones et causas emersuras
                        universaliter et generaliter examinare et diffinire, sententias executioni
                        mandare, rebelles et contumaces sua auctoritate bannire et aliter pro sua
                        voluntate punire, firmiter inhibentes, ne persona ulla magna vel parva
                        cuiuscumque dignitatis vel conditionis seu universitas insultum in
                        prescriptam Yporiensem ecclesiam, personas vel res eius facere presumat,
                        nostra nostrorumque successorum et totius dignitatis seu offitii hominum
                        contraditione remota. Ad hec regia auctoritate statuimus et ordinamus, ut
                        nulla prescriptio noceat vel possit obidi eidem ecclesie, nisi quinquaginta
                        annorum curriculis sit munita. Si quis igitur huius pagine nostre statuta et
                        ordinata presumpserit violare vel eis modo quolibet contraire, <rs key="#Penalty">mille
                            marcharum argenti</rs> reius existat, medietate <rs key="#Camera_regis">nobis</rs>, alia
                        medietate eidem ecclesie persolvenda. Huius rei <rs key="#Witness"
                            >testes</rs> fuerunt: <persName
                                key="#Witness #Imperial/royal_diploma #Archbishops" ref="#people/4060"><rs
                                key="#Archbishops">archiepiscopus</rs>
                            <placeName key="#Archbishops" ref="#places/2968"
                            >Maguntinus</placeName></persName>, <persName
                                key="#Witness #Imperial/royal_diploma #Archbishops" ref="#people/4061">archiepiscopus
                                <placeName key="#Archbishops" ref="#places/4452"
                                >Magdeburgensis</placeName></persName>, <persName
                                    key="#Witness #Imperial/royal_diploma #Bishops" ref="#people/4062">episcopus <placeName
                                key="#Bishops" ref="#places/1609"
                        >Warmacensis</placeName></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Imperial/royal_diploma #Bishops" ref="#people/4063">episcopus <placeName
                                key="#Bishops" ref="#places/8">Taurinensis</placeName></persName>,
                        imperialis aule vicarius, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Imperial/royal_diploma #Bishops">episcopus <placeName
                                key="#Bishops" ref="#places/245">Novariensis</placeName></persName>,
                        dux Saxonie, dux Braybantie, dux Bauuyre, marchio Montisferrati,
                                <persName><name ref="Warnerius de Bullanda"
                            >Warnerius</name></persName> et <persName><name
                                ref="Philippus de Bullanda">Phylippus</name></persName> de Bullanda
                        fratres, <persName><name ref="Anselmus de Iustino"
                            >Anselmus</name></persName> de Iustino imperialis aule marescalcus,
                                <persName><name ref="Ricardus camemarius">Ricardus</name></persName>
                        privatus domini regis <rs key="#Other_palatine_officer">camerarius</rs> et
                        plures alii. Ego <persName key="#Chancellor #Bishops" ref="#people/4059"
                            >Conradus</persName>
                        <placeName key="#Bishops" ref="#places/4451">Metensis</placeName> et
                            <placeName key="#Bishops #Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#places/2988"
                            >Spirensis</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs>, imperialis aule <rs key="#Chancellor"
                            >canzelarius</rs>, vidi et recognovi. Dat. apud Spiram, V kalendas
                        martii, anno ab incarnatione domini nostri Iesu Christi millesimo
                        duecentesimo, XVIIII, indictione VII, feliciter. </ab>
                </div>
